The paper deals with a combinatorial problem of packing graphs, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem involves finding a planar graph, which suggests computational geometry (cs.CG) as another likely sub-category. The use of trees and their properties in the problem indicates that algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) could also be relevant. The paper also presents a constructive proof and a polynomial time algorithm, which could be of interest to the sub-categories of graph theory (cs.GT) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
